==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adulterer
<hw>A*dul"ter*er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Formed fr. the
verb <ets>adulter</ets>, with the E. ending <ets>-er</ets>. See
<er>Advoutrer</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A man who commits adultery;
a married man who has sexual intercourse with a woman not his
wife.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Script.)</fld> <def>A man who violates his
religious covenant.</def> <rj><au>Jer. ix. 2.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adulteress</ent>⟦br⟧
